3:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["How Funding Works on ","Paradex"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex calculates TIA/USDT funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average price (TWAP) mechanism that compares the perpetual price to the underlying index. The funding payment occurs at the top of each hour, with long positions paying short positions when rates are positive, and vice versa when negative. Portfolio margin allows traders to use TIA positions as collateral for other trades, enabling capital-efficient funding rate strategies. The platform's StarkNet infrastructure provides transparent on-chain settlement while maintaining the speed required for active funding rate trading."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TIA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA represents Celestia's modular blockchain infrastructure token, which often exhibits funding rate patterns different from major cryptocurrencies due to its specialized use case and smaller market cap. The pair's mid-tier volume on Paradex creates opportunities for funding rate arbitrage, especially during periods of heightened interest in modular blockchain narratives. Celestia's role in the data availability layer ecosystem can drive sustained directional bias in perpetual positions, leading to persistent funding rate imbalances."}]]}],[["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"TIA Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA funding rates on Paradex typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per hour, with higher volatility during ecosystem announcements or major integrations. The token's infrastructure narrative creates periods of sustained long bias, particularly when new rollups adopt Celestia for data availability. Weekend funding rates often compress due to reduced institutional activity, while weekday sessions see more pronounced rate movements. The 1-hour funding frequency means daily rates can compound significantly during trending periods, making timing crucial for profitable arbitrage strategies."}]]}],["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable TIA funding arbitrage opportunities on Paradex occur during narrative-driven rallies when long interest significantly outweighs short positions. Cross-DEX arbitrage between Paradex and centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX can be particularly lucrative due to different user bases and funding calculation methods. Portfolio margin enables traders to hedge spot TIA holdings with short perpetual positions, capturing funding payments while maintaining delta exposure. The self-custodial nature means no withdrawal delays, allowing for rapid capital deployment when rate differentials emerge across venues."}]]}],"$L8"],"$L9"]}]
