8:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA's infrastructure token status means funding rates can shift rapidly during sector rotation or competitive threats from other data availability solutions. The relatively low liquidity compared to major cryptocurrencies increases the risk of slippage when entering or exiting large positions for funding rate capture. StarkNet's transaction finality, while generally reliable, can occasionally experience delays during network congestion, potentially affecting time-sensitive funding rate strategies. Traders should monitor Celestia network metrics and competing Layer 2 developments, as fundamental changes can quickly reverse funding rate trends and impact arbitrage profitability."}]]}]
9:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Paradex's 1-hour funding cycle affect TIA arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour funding cycle allows for more frequent rate resets compared to traditional 8-hour cycles, reducing the risk of prolonged adverse rates but requiring more active monitoring. This shorter cycle can amplify daily funding payments during trending periods but also provides more opportunities to exit positions if rates turn unfavorable."},{"question":"Can I use TIA tokens as collateral for funding rate trades on Paradex?","answer":"Yes, Paradex's portfolio margin system allows TIA spot holdings to serve as collateral for perpetual positions across all supported pairs. This enables capital-efficient strategies where you can earn funding payments on short TIA perps while holding the underlying token, though this creates concentrated exposure to TIA price movements."},{"question":"What are the main risks of TIA funding arbitrage on a StarkNet DEX?","answer":"Key risks include StarkNet transaction delays during network congestion, lower liquidity leading to higher slippage, and smart contract risks inherent to DEX trading. Additionally, TIA's infrastructure token classification means funding rates can be highly sensitive to competitive developments in the modular blockchain space."},{"question":"How do TIA funding rates on Paradex compare to centralized exchanges?","answer":"Paradex often shows higher funding rate volatility due to its smaller user base and different trader demographics compared to centralized exchanges. The 1-hour funding frequency versus 8-hour cycles on most CEXs creates different rate accumulation patterns, sometimes offering arbitrage opportunities between platforms with varying funding schedules."}]}]
